<div class="body" id="fhbody-174386259">
	
		
	

	
		
		<div id="text-174386259" class="p">
			
		 	
				An anonymous reader shares a report:<i> Apple has <a href="https://novayagazeta.eu/articles/2024/07/04/apple-bows-to-kremlin-pressure-to-remove-leading-vpns-from-russian-appstore-en-news">removed several apps offering virtual private network services</a> from the Russian App Store, following a request from Roskomnadzor, Russia's media regulator, independent news outlet Mediazona reported on Thursday.<br> <br>

The VPN services removed by Apple include leading services such as ProtonVPN, Red Shield VPN, NordVPN and Le VPN. Those living in Russia will no longer be able to download the services, while users who already have them on their phones can continue using them, but will be unable to update them. Red Shield VPN posted a notice from Apple on X, which said that their app would be removed following a request from Roskomnadzor, "because it includes content that is illegal in Russia."</i><br>
		 	
		</div>

		

		

		
			
		
	</div>
