		<div id="comment_body_64600717"><p>Sounds like a good idea until you consider people that have a real need for some of these things. Journalists and even those fighting communists from inside the country. You'd be cutting off their access to apps that allow them to continue their work safely.</p><p>In recent years, Apple has added features to iOS for these type of folks, allowing them to remain better protected when working in a hostile environment. And providing them access to things like VPN apps and others like encrypted messaging such as Signal, is critical to them. It can literally mean life or death for them.</p><p>It's also how their citizens can access information outside the country. It's how they can bypass the state-run propaganda. Without it, they're far more limited to the narrative that the Russian government is feeding them. These apps often provide a critical lifeline to millions and connection with the realities of what their country is doing.</p></div>
	</div>

